          by these Terms. If you do not agree, please do not use this Site.
        </p>

        <h2>1. Nature of This Website</h2>
        <p>
          This Site is a professional information website for Dr. Tal Lavian, Ph.D., an expert witness
          and consultant specializing in Telecommunications, Network Communications, Internet technologies,
          and related fields. The Site provides information about Dr. Lavian's qualifications, publications,
          presentations, case history, and professional services.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>This Site is intended for use by attorneys, law firms, corporate counsel, and other
          legal and technical professionals</strong> seeking information about expert witness and consulting
          services in patent litigation and related matters.
        </p>

        <h2>2. No Expert-Client Relationship Formed by Site Visit</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Accessing or using this Site does not establish any expert-client, consultant-client,
          or attorney-client relationship</strong> between you and TelecommNet Engineering, Inc. or
          Dr. Tal Lavian. No such relationship is formed until a written engagement letter or retainer
          agreement has been fully executed by both parties.
        </p>

        <h2>3. Informational Purpose Only</h2>
        <p>
          All content on this Site — including descriptions of services, case summaries, publication
          references, and credential information — is provided <strong>for informational purposes only</strong>.
          Nothing on this Site constitutes legal advice, technical advice, or an opinion on any specific
          matter. Site content should not be relied upon as a substitute for consultation with qualified
          legal counsel or technical experts in the context of a specific case or matter.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>
          All content on this Site — including text, layout, graphics, logos, publications, presentation
          materials, and the selection and arrangement of content — is the property of TelecommNet
          Engineering, Inc. or Dr. Tal Lavian and is protected by United States and international
          copyright, trademark, and intellectual property laws.
        </p>
        <p>
          You may view and print pages from this Site for your own personal, non-commercial, informational
          use in evaluating expert witness services. You may not:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Reproduce, republish, or redistribute Site content for commercial purposes without written permission.</li>
          <li>Modify or create derivative works based on Site content.</li>
          <li>Remove or alter any copyright, trademark, or proprietary notices.</li>
          <li>Use any Site content in a manner that misrepresents Dr. Lavian's qualifications, opinions,
              or affiliations.</li>
          <li>Scrape, crawl, or systematically extract content from this Site using automated tools,
              except as permitted by our robots.txt file for legitimate search engine indexing.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Scientific publications authored by Dr. Lavian that appear on this Site may be subject to
          separate copyright held by the respective publisher (ACM, IEEE, etc.). Please refer to the
          original publication venue for reproduction rights.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Expert Witness Engagement Terms</h2>
        <p>
          Any engagement of Dr. Tal Lavian as an expert witness, consulting expert, or technical consultant
          is subject to the following conditions:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Written Engagement Required:</strong> All engagements must be formalized through a
              written engagement letter or retainer agreement signed by both parties before any work commences.</li>
          <li><strong>Conflict Check:</strong> Prior to accepting any engagement, Dr. Lavian will conduct a
              conflict-of-interest review. Acceptance of any engagement is contingent on the absence of
              disqualifying conflicts.</li>
          <li><strong>Independence:</strong> Dr. Lavian provides independent expert opinions based on his
              technical expertise and review of case materials. Engagement as an expert witness does not
              guarantee any particular opinion or conclusion.</li>
          <li><strong>Fees:</strong> Fee schedules are provided upon request and are incorporated into the
              engagement letter. Retainer terms are specified in the engagement letter.</li>
          <li><strong>Confidentiality:</strong> Confidentiality obligations between the parties are
              addressed in the engagement letter.</li>
